# Data Cleaning
lobby1 <- tibble(file = paste0(c("lob_agency.txt"))) %>%
        mutate(text = map(file, read_lines)) %>%
        unnest() %>%
        group_by(file = str_sub(basename(file), 1, -5)) %>% 
        mutate(line_number = row_number()) %>%
        ungroup() %>%
        unnest_tokens(word, text) %>% 
        anti_join(stop_words) %>% ## remove stop words 
        mutate(word = wordStem(word)) ## stemming the words
## Warning: `cols` is now required.
## Please use `cols = c(text)`
## Joining, by = "word"
# Bing sentiment analysis
lobby1_sentiment <- lobby1 %>%
        inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>%
        count(word, sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>%
        ungroup()
## Joining, by = "word"
lobby1_sentiment
## # A tibble: 20 x 3
##    word    sentiment     n
##    <chr>   <chr>     <int>
##  1 protect positive  55422
##  2 vice    negative   5333
##  3 benefit positive   1340
##  4 thrift  positive   1155
##  5 hazard  negative    979
##  6 fine    positive    636
##  7 risk    negative    435
##  8 prison  negative    372
##  9 crime   negative    367
## 10 threat  negative    292
## 11 faith   positive    206
## 12 right   positive    130
## 13 toxic   negative    127
## 14 merit   positive     69
## 15 freedom positive     58
## 16 dead    negative     48
## 17 deaf    negative     33
## 18 debt    negative     28
## 19 support positive     22
## 20 correct positive     10
lobby1_sentiment %>%
        group_by(sentiment) %>%
        top_n(10) %>%
        ungroup() %>%
        mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>%
        ggplot(aes(word, n, fill = sentiment)) +
        geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
        facet_wrap(~sentiment, scales = "free_y") +
        labs(y = "Contribution to sentiment",
                x = NULL) +
        coord_flip()
## Selecting by n
